# 2026-05-06 v3.8.aae — BOL QR + email tracking link reliability fix.
# 2026-05-18 v3.8.add — /track + /verify retired as React routes, now
# served as static HTML. Rewrite the deep-link tokens to the static page;
# the static page's vanilla JS reads window.location.pathname and fetches.
# /tracking/* legacy splat: redirects historical email links to consolidated
# /track/<token> URL pattern (status 301, browser URL updates).
# /track/* SPA-rewrite splat: serves the track page for QR/bookmark deep-links.
# Status 200 preserves the URL so customers can bookmark.
# Closes CLAUDE.md §13.3 Item 31.
#
# 2026-06-12 v3.8.amx P0 — rewrite TARGET must be the extensionless path.
# With `/track.html` as the target, Cloudflare Pages normalizes the .html
# rewrite into a 308 redirect to /track, which DROPS the token splat:
# every BOL QR scan and email tracking link landed on the empty search
# page (verified live: /track/<token> → 308 → bare /track). Extensionless
# target `/track` serves track.html via Cloudflare's native fallback with
# the URL (and token) preserved — same proven pattern as /quote/approve/*
# below (verified live: 200, URL preserved). Bare /track never matches the
# splat, so the v3.8.ade redirect-loop class cannot fire.
/tracking/*    /track/:splat   301
/track/*       /track          200

# 2026-05-16 v3.8.abo — Sprint 51 Item 129 RC verification anti-fraud.
# 2026-05-18 v3.8.add — converted to static HTML mirroring /track pattern.
# /verify/<token> URLs land on /verify.html which reads the token from
# window.location.pathname and fetches /api/verify/:token. Status 200
# preserves the URL so the verification link printed on the RC PDF
# header remains bookmarkable.
#
# 2026-05-18 v3.8.ade — bare /track and /verify rules removed. Cloudflare
# Pages natively serves out/track.html at the path /track (and same for
# verify), so an explicit `/track /track.html 200` rule races with that
# internal canonicalization → ERR_TOO_MANY_REDIRECTS observed on first
# v3.8.add deploy. Splat rules below handle the deep-link token case
# (/track/<token> → /track.html); bare paths fall through to Cloudflare's
# native .html extension fallback, which is what we want.
#
# 2026-06-12 v3.8.amx P0 — same extensionless-target fix as /track/* above:
# the /verify.html target was 308-normalized and dropped the RC-PDF
# verification token.
/verify/*      /verify         200

# v3.8.akn §13.3 Item 180.4 — magic-link quote approval.
# /quote/approve/<token> → /quote/approve (status 200, URL preserved).
# Customer clicks the "Approve this quote" button in the quote email;
# the React page at /quote/approve reads the token from
# window.location.pathname + POSTs to /api/quote-approve. Same SPA-rewrite
# pattern as /track/* and /verify/* — Next.js static export can't
# pre-render arbitrary token paths, so all token-bearing URLs land on
# the same single static page and runtime-extract the token from URL.
/quote/approve/*  /quote/approve  200
